description: Numbers (not of the form 9n+-4) that were conjectured not to be the sum of 3 positive or negative cubes. However, further research suggests that this sequence is in fact empty.
comments: This sequence is incorrect. It is left in the database in case there are references or links to it.
references: R. K. Guy, Unsolved Problems in Number Theory, D5.
links: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Cubic Number.
mathematica: 30 is not in the sequence because Plus@@({-283059965, -2218888517, 2220422932}^3) gives 30.
